at a temperature of 100,000,000 celcius.<br>
For all Thermodynamic engines Ve increases by the<br>
sqaure root of the magnitude of the change in engine operating temperature.<br>
2500 C is the operating temperature of a nerva <br>
style ntr. For this reason vaismir by  using Hydrogen<br>
 as propellant can achieve a ve of 10 km/sec * <br>
the sqaure root of 100,000,000/2500 = the sqaure root<br>
of 40,000 which is 200. So Vasimir can yield ve =<br>
2000 km/sec which provides a specific impulse of<br>
200,000 seconds. It takes 200,000,000 watts of electric<br>
power to heat 1 gram of mass to this temperature <br>
assuming an efficiency of 50%. The electromagnetic<br>
body forces achieved inside of vasimirs' magnetic nozzle<br>
might double this to 4000 km/ sec  which is Si = 400,000<br>
seconds Averaging these numbers yield a mean average<br>
maximium  Ve of 3000 km sec foor it which is <br>
ve = .01c .<br>
This an example of why interplanetary propulsion<br>
will likely be dominated by nuclear electric ion drive,<br>
and plasma drive propulsion  systems in the future.<br>
Pulsed nuclear fusion drives are likley  to be used<br>
for non relatavistic star missions at perhaps<br>
V = .10 C to . 20 C<br>
