That’s alot of power bro, I love the plasma drive concept but<br>
If a more elegant solution can't be found a pressurized water-cooled reactor + steam turbine + generator about the size of the installation on an Ohio class submarine would be needed.<br>
<br>
I have seen one design that uses a vapor core reactor coupled with a MHD generator that pumps juice to a vasimir thruster and that might be the ticket.<br>
<br>
If we can get that lightweight vapor fueled reactor running at the power levels needed trips to the outer planets beyond mars become very reasonable. Even with a traditional pressurized reactor the concept has merit. If a 1/20 gee can be maintained for 16 hours that would provide about 29 km/sec. <br>
